modules.description: This module implements the Blake2b cryptographic hashing algorithm. It provides functions to initialize a hashing context, update it with data, and produce a final hash. It works with byte sequences for input data and keys, producing a hash value as output. Use cases include generating secure hashes for data integrity verification and key derivation.

This module implements the Blake2b cryptographic hash function, offering operations to initialize a hash state, update it with arbitrary byte sequences, and finalize the hash computation. It accepts input data and optional keys as byte arrays, producing a fixed-size hash digest. It is suitable for applications such as verifying data integrity, generating unique identifiers, and deriving cryptographic keys.
